.TH SERCON 1 "June 2026" "sercon" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sercon \- interactive serial console for Arduino and UART devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sercon
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sercon
connects your terminal to a serial device and forwards input/output in both directions.
It can list available serial ports, set baud rate, print timestamps on incoming lines,
and render ANSI styling when supported.
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -l , " --list"
List available serial ports and exit.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help text and exit.
.TP
.BR -p , " --port " PORT
Serial port to open
.TP
.BR -b , " --baud " BAUD
Set baud rate. Minimum accepted value is 9600.
Values below 9600 are clamped to 9600.
.TP
.BR -r , " --retry-delay"
Delay in seconds between connection retries (default: 1).
.TP
.BR -T , " --no-timestamps"
Disable timestamp prefix on incoming lines.
.TP
.BR -v , " --version"
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.BR -w , " --eof-wait"
Seconds to wait after EOF on stdin before exiting (default: 1).
.SH EXAMPLES
List ports:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --list
.RE
.PP
Show help:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --help
.RE
.PP
Connect at 9600 baud:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --port cu.usbmodem1101
.RE
.PP
Connect at 115200 baud:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon -p cu.usbmodem1101 -b 115200
.RE
.PP
Disable timestamps:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon -p cu.usbmodem1101 --no-timestamps
.RE
.PP
Print version:
.PP
.RS
.B sercon --version
.RE
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT
Ctrl+C triggers graceful shutdown.
.SH BEHAVIOR NOTES
.PP
Prompt text defaults to the selected port basename (or the executable name).
.PP
Prompt and cursor UI are shown only in interactive mode with ANSI enabled.
.PP
Carriage returns are ignored, and linefeeds define line/timestamp boundaries.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments, missing required port, or serial open/read error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stty (1),
.BR screen (1),
.BR picocom (1),
.BR minicom (1)
